cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.ROB, cs.MA, cs.EM 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper presents a new legged robot system with a focus on the actuator module and foot contact sensor design, as well as a novel controller for legged locomotion. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper discusses impedance and force control, and presents a controller for regulating complex motions. 
- cs.ROB (Robotics and Automation) is another possible category as the paper focuses on the design and assembly of a quadruped robot. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the potential for rapid distribution and duplication of the robot within the research community. 
- cs.EM (Engineering Mathematics) is also less likely but possible as the paper presents measurements of achieved impedance in static and dynamic scenarios.
